page.title: 20WOOBURN GREEN-CONCLUSION
page.content: Wooburn Green is an area of great beauty in the Wye Valley,with steeply sloping fields and lovely woodland.The major Geological deposit is chalk and flint stones abound.The R.Wye,a tributary of R.Thames was used once to power paper mills which no longer exist .It is joined to Bourne End which is the end of the R.Wye and is a fast growing community. In 1971 the population was 9,910 but had increased to 10,160 by 1981.The number of houses in the area have increased to 3,844 and this is due mainly to single occupants,one parent familys and retired people.It is a popular residential area because of easy access to London,the motorway and Heathrow airport.Wooburn Green is a pleasant community in which to live.
